THE documents contained in this volume have not been selected in the view of reviving or illustrating the ancient national* contro- versy as to the feudal dependence of Scotland on the English crown. Whatever indeed may be the merits of that question as matter of legal and constitutional enquiry, the proceedings here recorded are but little calculated to aid the historian or the antiquary in a fair and satisfactory solution of it.
